Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of generating control strategies for robotic vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of linear temporal logic (LTL) formulas and automata-based model checking suggests a strong connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The consideration of environmental constraints and the need to satisfy different parts of the mission points towards the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of algorithms for finding an optimal control strategy falls under the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL).
